    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - INJECTION PUMP, NOZZLES, FUEL FILTER, SUPPLY PUMP AND GLOW PLUGS -
        FUEL SUPPLY PUMP (Removal and Reassembly) (All applications)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FUEL SUPPLY PUMP (Removal and Reassembly) (All applications)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect hose from the fuel supply pump inlet and inverted flare tube connecting nut
                    from the fuel outlet. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_189.xml" xrefid="ef4350927">9.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the two bolts with washers
                    <emph type="bold">(Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_189.xml" xrefid="ef4350927">9.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) which fasten the fuel supply pump to the crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fuel supply pump. Be careful not to force or damage fuel supply pump arm upon
                    removal. Remove gasket and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
